            "content": {
                "raw": "Being able to specify `edgecolors` as an argument -- which I think would be better off as supplying a `plot_args` in general, as is done in other callbacks -- would mean any color could be used, not just the white colormap.  So the arguments could be either/or, with the cmap or with the edgecolors.",
                "html": "<p>Being able to specify <code>edgecolors</code> as an argument -- which I think would be better off as supplying a <code>plot_args</code> in general, as is done in other callbacks -- would mean any color could be used, not just the white colormap.  So the arguments could be either/or, with the cmap or with the edgecolors.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
